"Bottled on 11-12-14, nice and fresh from a SNOW PACK.  Poured into a tulip at 55 degrees.  Pours almost completely black, with highlights of black cherry under intense light.  Creamy light khaki colored head about 1.5 inches high, fading to a thin film with nice lacing on the glass.   Smells like light bean coffee with a malty sweet background - it's definitely a hearty stout beer smell. Cold-pressed coffee mouth feel, which feels nice.  It most definitely tastes like a delicious cup of high grade black coffee.  It has medium to high carbonation, but it doesn't overwhelm the flavor.  It's just lightweight enough to not be too filling, but dark and heavy enough to know I'm drinking a stout - mostly due to the pleasant but strong coffee flavor lingering on the palette. If you love coffee and beer, this one hits the mark.  Wish they sold 12 packs of this."
