"Got this beer in a winter variety pack and I am very impressed. Poured into a pint glass. Appearance: 2 finger light brown head and spotty lacing. Dark dark brown almost black, like iced coffee. Smell: immediately get hit with coffee, chocolate, hints of malt and caramel, and some piney notes of hops. Tate: coffee and chocolate, like mocha, malt, some dark fruits, and a hint of hops that comes in at the end followed by an aftertaste of coffee. Mouthfeel: medium carbonation, more carbonation than most stouts I have had which are more on the frothy side. Overall: absolutely delicious. Definitely a winter warmer. Just added this one too my list of beers that I get for traditions sake every winter."
