"Overall I thought this was a good beer and I thought it was a good example of the style, it had pretty much everything that I look for in the style and I enjoyed drinking it.  This beer had good drinkability, it was smooth, crisp, dry on the finish, not filling at all and the taste did a nice job at holding my attention, I could probably drink a few of these and I can't say that for many Coffee Stouts.  What I like the most about this beer was the how true to style it was and the drinkability, i thought they were the highlights of this beer.  What I liked the least about this beer was the body, i wish it was just a little thicker.  I would buy this beer again and it would be nice to be able to buy this on it's own and I think it makes for a great cold weather beer.  I would recommend this to anyone who likes Coffee Stouts, it's for sure worth a try.  All in all I was happy with this beer, it turned out to be a pretty good Coffee Stout and I think it can hold it's own in the style, but Founders Breakfast Stout is till my favorite of the style and it isn't my favorite Sierra Nevada beer, but I do think it's one of the better beers I've had from them.  Good job guys this was a tasty Coffee Stout and I think you guys made a good move putting this in the winter variety pack, keep up the good work."
