"Pours out jet black and leaves a small mocha head that dissipates rather fast while leaving beautiful lacing down the glass. Nice and roasty up front with a rich coffee, toffee, earthy, sweetness, and slight dark fruit. When trying it for the first time you get the roasted bitterness like the nose.  Then you pick up the sweet toffee, nuttiness, earthy hops, then in the finish i s some strong lingering coffee.  The body of the beer is medium to light and seems rather slick and dry.  I like my stouts a little fuller bodied then this.  Overall this is a really strong tasting coffee stout, not shying away from the full flavor of coffee here.  Not the best stout but an enjoyable one at that. If you like coffee and stouts look out for Sierra Nevada's snow pack, Cheers!"
