"i didnt get as much coffee out of this as i had hoped for, but thats about my only real critique of an otherwise beautiful beer. i think because their hoppy stuff is so good, that sierra nevada gets overlooked for their dark beer sometimes. not fair, this is really good. obsidian black with a similar shine and over an inch of lasting mocha bubble lace on top. more roast than coffee on the nose, although the coffee is there in the back with a dried fruit character to it. im surprised the body is as light as it is, not to say its light, but that its not thick and heavy like stouts can be. not sure if i dig that or not, but it is immediately noticeable. dark chalky malts meet some caramel sweetness in the middle, its very well rounded in its grain base. the coffee is subtle and its all in the finish, i could stand to see this ramped up just a bit, but i like it as an accent flavor too. the beer tastes rich but feels quite delicate, lending to drinkability. nice cold weather beer, i always like the one off stuff in these mix boxes they do. this is a good one."
