"Bottle. Pours very black with any in, tan head. Light lacing. Aroma is coffee forward with a milky note. Cold brew coffee. Roasty and just a tad bit chocolatey. The flavor clearly coffee-driven but it lacks much bitterness that I usually up equate to genuine coffee flavor. It isn't necessarily a bad thing. Coffee with cream and sugar. Finishes fairly sweet. Medium bodied. Actually very easy to slurp back. Pretty good, especially for a presumed one-off beer in a mix-pack."
